import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.scatterplot(data=data, x='u', y='v')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of x and y coordinates in the dataset?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    sns.boxplot(data=data, orient='h', palette='Set2', ax=ax)
    ax.set_title('What is the range of x and y coordinates in the dataset?', wrap=True)
    ax.set_xlabel('Coordinate Value')
    ax.set_ylabel('Coordinate Axis')
    ax.legend(['u', 'v'], title='Axis', loc='upper right')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sns.scatterplot(x='u', y='v', data=data)
    sns.regplot(x='u', y='v', data=data, scatter=False, color='red', label='Regression Line')
    plt.title('What is the correlation between x and y coordinates in the dataset?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 8))
    heatmap = sns.kdeplot(data=data, x='u', y='v', cmap='viridis', shade=True)
    plt.title('What is the density of points in different regions of the 2D plane?', wrap=True)
    cbar = heatmap.figure.colorbar(heatmap.collections[0])
    cbar.set_label('Density')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import numpy as np

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    # Calculate the distances between all points
    distances = []
    for i in range(len(data)):
        for j in range(i+1, len(data)):
            distance = np.sqrt((data.iloc[i]['u'] - data.iloc[j]['u'])**2 + (data.iloc[i]['v'] - data.iloc[j]['v'])**2)
            distances.append(distance)

    # Plot the histogram of distances
    plt.hist(distances, bins=30, color='blue', alpha=0.7, label='Distances')
    plt.xlabel('Distance')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of distances between points in the dataset?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
